2015;;Across the Line;;Canadian;;Director X;;Stefan James, Sarah Jeffery, Shamier Anderson;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Across_the_Line_(2015_film);;The film is set in North Preston, Nova Scotia where Mattie (Stephan James), a black hockey player, is being considered for a professional career. However, his hopes are threatened by growing racial strife at his school while his brother Carter (Shamier Anderson) is involved in criminal activity. Mattie also has a romantic interest in Jayme (Sarah Jeffery) who already has a white boyfriend.[2]<br><br>The film's storyline was inspired by the 1989 Cole Harbour District High School race riots.[3]